TensorFlow Playground does not provide direct code snippets for loading CSV datasets, as it is primarily a GUI-based tool. However, you can use JavaScript with libraries like D3.js or Papa Parse to load and preprocess CSV data before feeding it into a model. Here’s an example of how you might load a CSV file using JavaScript:
javascript
// Example using Papa Parse to load CSV data
Papa.parse("your_data.csv", {
  header: true,
  complete: function(results) {
    const data = results.data;
    // Extract input features and output
    const inputs = data.map(row => [parseFloat(row.input1), parseFloat(row.input2)]);
    const outputs = data.map(row => parseFloat(row.output));
    // Use inputs and outputs for training
  }
});
